SIMPLE: sappy
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sappy
<hw>Sap"py</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Sappier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Sappiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[From 1st <er>Sap</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Abounding with sap; full of sap; juicy;
succulent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, young, not firm; weak, feeble.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When he had passed this weak and <qex>sappy</qex> age.</q>
<rj><qau>Hayward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Weak in intellect.</def> <mark>[Low]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Abounding in sap; resembling, or
consisting largely of, sapwood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sappy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sappy
<hw>Sap"py</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>sapy</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[Cf. L. <ets>sapere</ets> to
taste.]</ety> <def>Musty; tainted.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saprophagan</ent>⟦br⟧
